The Greytown regional court has convicted and sentenced former Umvoti municipality traffic officer Dumisani Mchunu (45) to four years’ imprisonment for corruption. According to a statement released by the Hawks, Mchunu demanded R10 000 gratification after he claimed that the license disc of the complainant’s vehicle was fraudulent. “The complainant reported the matter to the Hawks members from the Durban Serious Corruption Investigation Unit and an undercover operation was conducted on March 3,” read the statement. It added that Mchunu was arrested at his place of employment and charged with corruption. “He appeared in court several times until he was convicted and sentenced,” read the statement. Mchunu was sentenced to four years’ imprisonment, half of which will be served under correctional supervision.